<br>
Rangers and Orc Dangers <br>
by Alan Denny    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> Strategy:<br>
<br>
Fellowship:  First things first, bid high play Sam from your draw deck exert him three times to remove burdens and then forfeit him to the first large minion you face.  You should play everything you get holding only the Versatilities and Statures for extreme use.  With heavily armed Companions and a nice supply of archery you should move as quickly as possible down the adventure path.  The usual move would betaking the sites in this order on each turn: 1st 1-3, 2nd 4-5, 3rd 6-8, 4th finish at site 9.   Use Thror&#8217;s Map to replace your own sites as necessary.  Remember you want to be in the Forrest and at the rivers to exhaust minions.  <br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
Sauren Orc are truly nasty with some nasty abilities.  Even if all you have is a small tracker the bowmen can do a great deal of damage.  All of the trackers lower the roaming costs of your orcs so they become cheaper.  The direct damage the fellowship will take will keep them from moving fast.  Use the Hates to kill off companion that are exhausted, but make sure you save the hates to kill them not just wound them.  If by chance they make it to site 9 play as many minions from your hand as you can and then unload three trackers from you discard pile.  Even if you only save three twilight, three orc ambushers are nothing to sneeze at when mixed with other minions.  You should easily be able to overwhelm the fellowship.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21480"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21480" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
